<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e109714.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Male of P. turcicus sp. nov. A Habitus. B Anterior region of prosoma, lateral. Abbreviations: ctf - cheliceral transverse folds. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/889501" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e109714.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. P. turcicus sp. nov. A Chelicerae of female, ventral. B Spinnerets of female, ventral. C Habitus, female. D Male palp, ventral. Abbreviations: c - conductor, cl - colulus, ctf - cheliceral transverse folds, e - embolus, ma - median apophysis, t - tegulum. Scale bars: 1.00 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B); 1 mm (C); 0.3 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/889502" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e109714.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Male palp of P. turcicus sp. nov. A Ventral. B Dorsal. C Prolateral. D Retrolateral. Abbreviations: c - conductor, e - embolus, eb - embolic base, ma - median apophysis, pa - patellar apophysis, Ti - tibia. Scale bar: 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/889503" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e109714.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Epigyne and vulva of P. turcicus sp. nov. A Epigyne, ventral. B Macerated epigyne, ventral. C Vulva, dorsal. D Vulva, lateral. E Vulva, anterior. F Vulva, posterior. Abbreviations: cd - copulatory duct, co - copulatory opening, ef - epigastric furrow, fd - fertilisation duct, fo - fovea, mp - median plate, om - opaque membrane, s - spermatheca. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/889504" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e109714.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Distribution map of Paracedicus spp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/889505" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e109714.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. The type locality of P. turcicus sp. nov.; Mus Province, Korkut District, Konakduezue Village." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/889506" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

